; ── SYNTHETIC PLACEHOLDER SEQUENCES ──────────────────────────────────────
;
; These sequences are NOT real pylS or mttB sequences.
; They are synthetic DNA strings used only to demonstrate the tool's API.
;
; To obtain verified pyrrolysine-encoding sequences from M. acetivorans C2A:
;   Genome:  GenBank AE010299.1
;   pylS  :  locus MA3749  https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/1482527
;   mttB  :  locus MA0859  (trimethylamine methyltransferase, contains internal UAG)
;             https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/1480067
;
; For additional pyrrolysine-encoding genes, search GenBank AE010299.1
; for genes containing in-frame UAG codons (mtmB, mttB family).
;
; Quick download:
;   efetch -db nuccore -id AE010299.1 -format fasta > M_acetivorans.fasta
; ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; --- Synthetic mid-ORF UAG (pyrrolysine candidate context) ---
; Structure: ATG + 20x GCG codons + TAG + 15x GCG codons + GCGCGG stem-loop-like + TGA
>SYNTHETIC_MID_ORF_UAG_placeholder
ATGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCG
TAGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCG
GCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCCCCGGGGCCCCGGGGAAAAT
GCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGTGA

; --- Synthetic terminal UAG (stop codon context) ---
>SYNTHETIC_TERMINAL_UAG_placeholder
ATGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGGCGTAG
